            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-09T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="1030" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.5461/12–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bacon</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-09T20:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1291. RefEmbtel 2561 Dec. 8. Dept’s opinion little would be gained by refusing
                    accept Arbitration Comite decision and carrying question responsibility
                    settlement club labor dispute to People’s Court. Likely that such action wld
                    merely prolong Soule’s detention since doubtful People’s Court wld reverse
                    Arbitration Comite position. Dept and Army recommend acceptance decision
                    Arbitration Comite re responsibility for settlement. No objection ur compliance
                    terms as outlined Embtel 2556, Dec. 8.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
